OL,3,CFood prices, energy bills and
OL,4,Cpensions: What is the impact of the
OL,5,CIran war?
OL,7,FThe new energy price cap rules are
OL,8,Falso still set to come into force on
OL,9,FApril 1, making energy bills cheaper
OL,10,Fin the short term, but the cap is
OL,11,Fadjusted on a quarterly basis, which
OL,12,Fmeans the Iran conflict will be
OL,13,Freflected in whatever cap is set for
OL,14,FJuly 1.
OL,16,FThe latest cap, starting in April,
OL,17,Fwill drop from the current #1,758 to
OL,18,F#1,641 - a reduction of around #10 a
OL,19,Fmonth for the average household using
OL,20,Fboth electricity and gas.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
